TY  - JOUR
T1  - Interpersonal and Interaction Influences on Informal Resource Exchanges Between R&D Researchers Across Organizational Boundaries
AU  - Bouty, Isabelle
Y1  - 2000/02/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/1556385
DO  - 10.5465/1556385
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 50
EP  - 65
VL  - 43
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Though key to fostering innovation, interpersonal exchanges of resources between R&D scientists across organizational boundaries can represent intellectual capital leaks. A grounded theoretical framework is developed for individual exchange decisions. Social capital emerges as the key success factor in this resources acquisition process. Strategic resources can only be exchanged under conditions of acquaintance and mutual trust. The economic interests of a scientist's employing firm and personal considerations are intertwined.
AB  - Though key to fostering innovation, interpersonal exchanges of resources between R&D scientists across organizational boundaries can represent intellectual capital leaks. A grounded theoretical framework is developed for individual exchange decisions. Social capital emerges as the key success factor in this resources acquisition process. Strategic resources can only be exchanged under conditions of acquaintance and mutual trust. The economic interests of a scientist's employing firm and personal considerations are intertwined.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/1556385
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/1556385
